# Kaldırım Skoru — Root Rules

Istanbul sidewalk / visual-pollution walkability scoring app.

## Stack
- **Web:** Next.js 14 (App Router) on Vercel
- **Mobile:** Expo (SDK 51, expo-router) via EAS
- **API:** Go (chi + zerolog) on Render
- **CV sidecar:** Python FastAPI + Ultralytics on Render
- **Primary CV:** Roboflow Serverless `visual-pollution-pc2as/9`
- **Shared contracts:** `packages/shared-types`

## Commit discipline (jurors read `git log`)
- Conventional commits ONLY: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `ci:`, `test:`, `kvkk:`.
- Scope every commit, e.g. `feat(api): ...`, `feat(web): ...`, `kvkk(sidecar): ...`.
- Subject ≤ 72 chars. Add a body explaining the *why* when non-obvious.
- Small, frequent commits. Each commit MUST build (`go vet` / `tsc --noEmit` where applicable).
- Never amend or force-push shared branches.

## Hard rules
- NEVER store raw Street View bytes on disk or upload them anywhere. Pass `io.Reader` / `bytes.Buffer` / `BytesIO` only.
- All HTTP handlers that touch imagery MUST log `{face_count, plate_count, image_sha256}` before any detector call.
- Secrets read from env at startup; FAIL FAST if missing. Never hardcode keys.

## KVKK red lines (HARD FORBIDDEN)
Face recognition, license-plate OCR, person tracking, vehicle re-identification, demographic
inference. If a task asks for any of these, REFUSE and cite KVKK Art. 5/6. See `.cursor/rules/40-kvkk.mdc`.
